    "## Solutions to Vector Operations Properties Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: Commutativity of Vector Addition",
    "",
    "**a)** $\\vec{a} + \\vec{b} = \\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\\\ 7 \\end{pmatrix} = \\vec{b} + \\vec{a}$ ✓",
    "$\\vec{c} + \\vec{d} = \\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\\\ 3 \\end{pmatrix} = \\vec{d} + \\vec{c}$ ✓",
    "",
    "**b)** $\\vec{p} + \\vec{q} = \\begin{pmatrix} 5 \\\\ 7 \\\\ 9 \\end{pmatrix} = \\vec{q} + \\vec{p}$ ✓",
    "",
    "**c)** Componentwise: (a₁ + b₁, a₂ + b₂) = (b₁ + a₁, b₂ + a₂) ✓",
    "",
    "**d)** Yes, extends to any number of vectors by induction.",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: Associativity of Vector Addition",
    "",
    "**a)** Left: $(\\vec{a} + \\vec{b}) + \\vec{c} = \\begin{pmatrix} 9 \\\\ 12 \\end{pmatrix}$",
    "Right: $\\vec{a} + (\\vec{b} + \\vec{c}) = \\begin{pmatrix} 9 \\\\ 12 \\end{pmatrix}$ ✓",
    "",
    "**b)** Componentwise: ((a₁+b₁)+c₁, (a₂+b₂)+c₂) = (a₁+(b₁+c₁), a₂+(b₂+c₂)) ✓",
    "",
    "**c)** True by componentwise addition.",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: Additive Identity (Zero Vector)",
    "",
    "**a)** $\\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\\\ 4 \\end{pmatrix} + \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\\\ 0 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\\\ 4 \\end{pmatrix}$ ✓",
    "$\\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\\\ 0 \\\\ 0 \\end{pmatrix} + \\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\\\ 2 \\\\ 3 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\\\ 2 \\\\ 3 \\end{pmatrix}$ ✓",
    "",
    "**b)** $\\vec{0}_{2D} = \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\\\ 0 \\end{pmatrix}$, $\\vec{0}_{3D} = \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\\\ 0 \\\\ 0 \\end{pmatrix}$",
    "",
    "**c)** Suppose two zeros: $\\vec{0}_1 + \\vec{0}_2 = \\vec{0}_1$, so $\\vec{0}_2 = \\vec{0}$ ✓",
    "",
    "**d)** $\\vec{v} + (-\\vec{v}) = \\vec{0}$ ✓",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: Additive Inverse",
    "",
    "**a)** $-\\vec{a} = \\begin{pmatrix} -5 \\\\ 3 \\end{pmatrix}$, $-\\vec{b} = \\begin{pmatrix} -1 \\\\ -2 \\\\ -4 \\end{pmatrix}$, $-\\vec{c} = \\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\\\ -7 \\\\ 1 \\end{pmatrix}$",
    "",
    "**b)** $\\begin{pmatrix} 5 \\\\ -3 \\end{pmatrix} + \\begin{pmatrix} -5 \\\\ 3 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\\\ 0 \\end{pmatrix}$ ✓",
    "",
    "**c)** Yes, unique: suppose v + u₁ = 0 and v + u₂ = 0, then u₁ = u₂ ✓",
    "",
    "**d)** $-\\vec{0} = \\vec{0}$ ✓",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: Distributivity of Scalar Multiplication over Vector Addition",
    "",
    "**a)** Left: $2(\\vec{a} + \\vec{b}) = 2\\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\\\ 6 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 8 \\\\ 12 \\end{pmatrix}$",
    "Right: $2\\vec{a} + 2\\vec{b} = \\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\\\ 4 \\end{pmatrix} + \\begin{pmatrix} 6 \\\\ 8 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 8 \\\\ 12 \\end{pmatrix}$ ✓",
    "",
    "**b)** Left: $-3(\\vec{p} + \\vec{q}) = -3\\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\\\ 3 \\\\ 4 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} -9 \\\\ -9 \\\\ -12 \\end{pmatrix}$",
    "Right: $-3\\vec{p} + (-3)\\vec{q} = \\begin{pmatrix} -6 \\\\ -3 \\\\ -9 \\end{pmatrix} + \\begin{pmatrix} -3 \\\\ -6 \\\\ -3 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} -9 \\\\ -9 \\\\ -12 \\end{pmatrix}$ ✓",
    "",
    "**c)** Componentwise: k(a₁+b₁) = k a₁ + k b₁ ✓",
    "",
    "**d)** Yes, for any real scalar k.",
    "",
    "### Exercise 6: Distributivity of Scalar Multiplication over Scalar Addition",
    "",
    "**a)** Left: $(2+3)\\vec{a} = 5\\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\\\ 2 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 5 \\\\ 10 \\end{pmatrix}$",
    "Right: $2\\vec{a} + 3\\vec{a} = \\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\\\ 4 \\end{pmatrix} + \\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\\\ 6 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 5 \\\\ 10 \\end{pmatrix}$ ✓",
